Aethalops.label: Aethalops
Aethalops.description:
Aethalops is a genus of megabat in the Pteropodidae family. It contains the following species
Borneo Fruit Bat, Aethalops aequalis
Pygmy Fruit Bat, Aethalops alecto Wikipedia

African bush squirrel.label: African bush squirrel
African bush squirrel.description: The African bush squirrels are a genus, Paraxerus, squirrels of the subfamily Xerinae. They are only found in Africa. Wikipedia

Żubroń.label: Żubroń
Żubroń.description: Żubroń is a hybrid of domestic cattle and wisent. The wisent is the European bison; hence, the żubroń is analogous to the American beefalo. Wikipedia

Amazon black howler.label: Amazon black howler
Amazon black howler.description: The Amazon black howler is a species of howler monkey, a type of New World monkey, endemic to the south-central Amazon in Brazil. Wikipedia

Amebelodon.label: Amebelodon
Amebelodon.description: Amebelodon is a member of a diverse group of primitive proboscideans called gomphotheres, a group that also gave rise to the modern elephants and their close relative the mammoth. Wikipedia

Angolan slender mongoose.label: Angolan slender mongoose
Angolan slender mongoose.description: The Angolan slender mongoose is a mongoose that lives in southern Africa, specifically Angola and Namibia. It lives in the savannah and avoids desert and dense forests. Wikipedia

Anomalurus.label: Anomalurus
Anomalurus.description: Anomalurus is the largest genus in the rodent family Anomaluridae, with four species. It is the only genus in the subfamily Anomalurinae. Wikipedia

Arctic ground squirrel.label: Arctic ground squirrel
Arctic ground squirrel.description: The Arctic ground squirrel is a species of ground squirrel native to the Arctic. People in Alaska, particularly around the Aleutians, refer to them as "Parka" squirrels. Wikipedia

Aulophyseter.label: Aulophyseter
Aulophyseter.description: Aulophyseter is an extinct genus of sperm whale from the Miocene formations of the West and East coasts of North America as well as the Patagonian region of South America. It is a possible synonym of some fossils assigned to Orycterocetus. Wikipedia

Atlantic titi.label: Atlantic titi
Atlantic titi.description: The Atlantic Titi or Masked Titi, Callicebus personatus, is a species of titi, a type of New World monkey, endemic to Brazil. Wikipedia

Banded palm civet.label: Banded palm civet
Banded palm civet.description: The banded palm civet, also called the banded civet, is a civet found in the Sundaic region and occurs in peninsular Myanmar, peninsular Malaysia, peninsular Thailand and in Indonesia on the islands of Sipura, Sumatra and Borneo. Wikipedia

Bandicota.label: Bandicota
Bandicota.description: Bandicota is a genus of rodent from Asia. They are known as the bandicoot rats. Wikipedia

Banded surili.label: Banded surili
Banded surili.description: The banded surili is a species of primate in the Cercopithecidae family. It is endemic to the Thai-Malay Peninsula and the Indonesia island of Sumatra. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Baptista Lake titi.label: Baptista Lake titi
Baptista Lake titi.description: The Baptista Lake titi, Callicebus baptista, is a species of titi, a type of New World monkey, endemic to Brazil. Wikipedia

Barbara Brown's titi.label: Barbara Brown's titi
Barbara Brown's titi.description: Barbara Brown's titi is a species of titi, a type of New World monkey. This critically endangered species is endemic to the Caatinga in northeastern Brazil, and it is estimated that less than 250 mature individuals remain. Wikipedia

Angwantibo.label: Angwantibo
Angwantibo.description: Angwantibos are the two species of strepsirrhine primates that are classified in the genus Arctocebus of the family Lorisidae. They are also known as golden pottos because of their yellow or golden coloration. Wikipedia

Barylambda.label: Barylambda
Barylambda.description: Barylambda is an extinct genus of pantodont mammal from the middle to late Paleocene, well known from several finds in North America. Three species of Barylambda are currently recognised. Wikipedia

Bathyergus.label: Bathyergus
Bathyergus.description: Bathyergus is the genus of dune mole rats endemic to South Africa. It contains two species — B. janetta, the Namaqua Dune Mole Rat, and B. suillus, the Cape Dune Mole Rat. Wikipedia

Binturong.label: Binturong
Binturong.description: The binturong, also known as bearcat, is a viverrid native to South and Southeast Asia. It is uncommon in much of its range, and listed as Vulnerable by IUCN because of a declining population trend that ... Wikipedia

Bengal fox.label: Bengal fox
Bengal fox.description: The Bengal fox, also known as the Indian fox, is a fox endemic to the Indian subcontinent and is found from the Himalayan foothills and Terai of Nepal through southern India and from southern and eastern ... Wikipedia

Black-headed spider monkey.label: Black-headed spider monkey
Black-headed spider monkey.description: The black-headed spider monkey, Ateles fusciceps, is a species of spider monkey, a type of New World monkey, from Central and South America. It is found in Colombia, Nicaragua and Panama. Wikipedia

Black-footed cat.label: Black-footed cat
Black-footed cat.description: The black-footed cat is the smallest African cat, and is endemic in the south west arid zone of the southern African subregion. It is one of the lesser studied African carnivores, and is listed as Vulnerable by IUCN since 2002. Wikipedia

Black howler.label: Black howler
Black howler.description: The black howler is a species of howler monkey, a large New World monkey, from northeastern Argentina, eastern Bolivia, eastern and southern Brazil, and Paraguay. Together with the brown howler, it is the southernmost member of the Alouatta genus. Wikipedia

Blarinomys.label: Blarinomys
Blarinomys.description: Blarinomys breviceps, also known as the Brazilian shrew-mouse or the blarinine akodont, is a rodent in the tribe Akodontini from the Atlantic Forest of eastern and southeastern Brazil. It is the only species in the genus Blarinomys. Wikipedia

Blue-eyed black lemur.label: Blue-eyed black lemur
Blue-eyed black lemur.description: The blue-eyed black lemur, also known as the Sclater's lemur, is a species of true lemur. It can attain a body length of 39–45 cm, a tail length of 51–65 cm- a total length of 90–100 cm, and a weight of 1.8-1.9 kg. Wikipedia

Black titi.label: Black titi
Black titi.description: The black titi is a species of titi, a type of New World monkey, from South America. It is found in Brazil, Colombia, and Venezuela. Wikipedia

Bolivian red howler.label: Bolivian red howler
Bolivian red howler.description: The Bolivian red howler is a species of howler monkey, a type of New World monkey, endemic to Bolivia. It can be found in rain forests, including riverine and seasonally flooded forests. Wikipedia

Bongolava mouse lemur.label: Bongolava mouse lemur
Bongolava mouse lemur.description: The Bongolava mouse lemur is a species of mouse lemur endemic to Madagascar. It lives in western deciduous forest within a limited range, including Bongolava Forest and Ambodimahabibo Forest between the Sofia River and the Mahajamba River. Wikipedia

Bornean ferret-badger.label: Bornean ferret-badger
Bornean ferret-badger.description: The Bornean ferret-badger, also known as the Everett's ferret-badger or Kinabalu ferret-badger, is a member of the Mustelidae family. The scientific name commemorates British colonial administrator and zoological collector Alfred Hart Everett. Wikipedia

Branisella.label: Branisella
Branisella.description: Branisella is an extinct genus of New World monkey from the Salla formation of what is now Bolivia during the late Oligocene, approximately 26 million years ago. It is the oldest fossil New World Monkey discovered. Wikipedia

Bornean slow loris.label: Bornean slow loris
Bornean slow loris.description: The Bornean slow loris or Philippine slow loris is a strepsirrhine primate and a species of slow loris that is native to the north and east coastal areas of the island of Borneo, as well as the Sulu Archipelago in the Philippines. Wikipedia

Brown greater galago.label: Brown greater galago
Brown greater galago.description: The brown greater galago, also known as the large-eared greater galago, is a nocturnal primate, the largest in the family of galagos. Wikipedia

Brown titi.label: Brown titi
Brown titi.description: The brown titi is a species of titi, a type of New World monkey, from South America. It is found in Brazil, Peru, and Bolivia. Wikipedia

Booted macaque.label: Booted macaque
Booted macaque.description: The booted macaque is a macaque of the Sulawesi Island, Indonesia. This Old World monkey is diurnal and spends most of the day in the trees. It is 50–59 cm long plus a tail of 35–40 cm. Wikipedia

Brumback's night monkey.label: Brumback's night monkey
Brumback's night monkey.description: Brumback's night monkey is a species of night monkey found in Colombia. It has traditionally been considered a subspecies of gray-bellied night monkey, Aotus lemurinus. but it has recently been argued that it should be considered a separate species. Wikipedia

Brush-furred mouse.label: Brush-furred mouse
Brush-furred mouse.description: The brush-furred mice, genus Lophuromys are a peculiar group of rodents found in sub-Saharan Africa. They are members of the subfamily Deomyinae, a group only identifiable through molecular analysis. Wikipedia

Brush-tailed porcupine.label: African brush-tailed porcupine
Brush-tailed porcupine.description: The African Brush-Tailed Porcupine is a species of rat-like Old World porcupine called "brush-tailed porcupines". The brush-tailed porcupines live in forests, usually at high elevations. Wikipedia

Burrunan dolphin.label: Burrunan dolphin
Burrunan dolphin.description: The Burrunan dolphin is a species of bottlenose dolphin found in parts of Victoria, Australia. It was recognised as a species in 2011. Wikipedia

Callithrix.label: Callithrix
Callithrix.description: Callithrix is a genus of New World monkeys of the family Callitrichidae, the family containing marmosets and tamarins. The genus contains the Atlantic Forest marmosets. Wikipedia

California sea lion.label: California sea lion
California sea lion.description: The California sea lion is a coastal eared seal native to western North America. It is one of five species of sea lion. Its natural habitat ranges from southeast Alaska to central Mexico, including the Gulf of California. Wikipedia

Canariomys.label: Canariomys
Canariomys.description: Canariomys is an extinct genus of rodents that once existed on the islands of Tenerife and Gran Canaria, part of the Canary Islands, Spain. These giant rats could reach a weight of about 1 kg. Wikipedia

Cape genet.label: Cape genet
Cape genet.description: The Cape genet, also known as the blotched genet, large-spotted genet or muskeljaatkat in Afrikaans, is a carnivore mammal, related to the African linsang and to the civets. It lives only in South Africa. Wikipedia

Cacomistle.label: Cacomistle
Cacomistle.description: The cacomistle, Bassariscus sumichrasti, is a nocturnal, arboreal and omnivorous member of the carnivoran family Procyonidae. Wikipedia

Caribbean monk seal.label: Caribbean monk seal
Caribbean monk seal.description: The Caribbean monk seal, west Indian seal, or sea wolf, as early explorers referred to it, was a species of seal native to the Caribbean and now believed to be extinct. The Caribbean monk seals' main predators were sharks and humans. Wikipedia

Callosciurinae.label: Callosciurinae
Callosciurinae.description: Callosciurinae is an Asiatic subfamily of squirrels. It contains over 60 species, mostly found in South East Asia. It is named after the genus Callosciurus, which means 'Beautiful Squirrels'. Wikipedia

Celebes crested macaque.label: Celebes crested macaque
Celebes crested macaque.description: The Celebes crested macaque, also known as the crested black macaque, Sulawesi crested macaque, or the black ape, is an Old World monkey that lives in the northeast of the Indonesian island of Sulawesi as well as on smaller neighboring islands. Wikipedia

Chiriqui olingo.label: Northern olingo
Chiriqui olingo.description: The northern olingo, also known as the bushy-tailed olingo or as simply the olingo, is a tree-dwelling member of the family Procyonidae, which also includes raccoons. Wikipedia

Chlorocebus.label: Chlorocebus
Chlorocebus.description: Chlorocebus is a genus of medium-sized primates from the family of Old World monkeys. Six species are currently recognized, although some classify them all as a single species with numerous subspecies. Wikipedia

Claire's mouse lemur.label: Claire's mouse lemur
Claire's mouse lemur.description: Claire's mouse lemur, or Nosy Be mouse lemur, is a newly described species of lemur from the genus of the mouse lemurs. Wikipedia

Chrotomys.label: Chrotomys
Chrotomys.description: The genus Chrotomys contain a unique group of rodents found only in the Philippines, specifically the islands of Luzon, Mindoro, and Sibuyan. Wikipedia

Clouded leopard.label: Clouded leopard
Clouded leopard.description: The clouded leopard is a cat found from the Himalayan foothills through mainland Southeast Asia into China, and has been classified as Vulnerable in 2008 by IUCN. Wikipedia

Colobinae.label: Colobinae
Colobinae.description: The Colobinae are a subfamily of the Old World monkey family that includes 59 species in 10 genera, including the black-and-white colobus, the large-nosed proboscis monkey, and the gray langurs. Wikipedia

Coppery titi.label: Coppery titi
Coppery titi.description: The coppery titi is a species of titi, a type of New World monkey, from South America. It is found in the Amazon of Brazil and Peru, and perhaps Bolivia. Wikipedia

Coryphodon.label: Coryphodon
Coryphodon.description:
Coryphodon is an extinct genus of mammal.
Coryphodon was a pantodont, a member of the world's first group of large browsing mammals. It migrated across what is now northern North America, replacing Barylambda, an earlier pantodont. Wikipedia

Corynorhinus.label: Corynorhinus
Corynorhinus.description: The genus Corynorhinus consists of the lump-nosed bats, or American long-eared bats. Only three species occur in the genus, all occurring in North America. Members of this group were previously in the genus Plecotus. Wikipedia

Cozumel Island coati.label: Cozumel Island coati
Cozumel Island coati.description: The Cozumel Island coati is a coati from the Mexican island of Cozumel. It is in the family Procyonidae, which also includes raccoons, olingos, and kinkajous. Wikipedia

Crabeater seal.label: Crabeater seal
Crabeater seal.description: The crabeater seal is a true seal with a circumpolar distribution around the coast of Antarctica. They are medium- to large-sized, relatively slender and pale-colored, found primarily on the free-floating ... Wikipedia

Crab-eating mongoose.label: Crab-eating mongoose
Crab-eating mongoose.description: The crab-eating mongoose is a mongoose species ranging from the northeastern Indian subcontinent to Southeast Asia, southern China and Taiwan. It is listed as Near Threatened by IUCN. Wikipedia

Cricetulus.label: Cricetulus
Cricetulus.description:
Cricetulus is a genus of rodent in the family, Cricetidae. It has seven member species. They inhabit arid or semi-arid regions in Eurasia.
They tend to be more ratlike in appearance than typical hamsters, hence the common name "ratlike hamster." Wikipedia

Cetotherium.label: Cetotherium
Cetotherium.description: Cetotherium is a genus of extinct cetaceans from the family Cetotheriidae. Wikipedia

Crescent nail-tail wallaby.label: Crescent nail-tail wallaby
Crescent nail-tail wallaby.description: The crescent nail-tail wallaby was a nail-tail wallaby that lived in the woodlands and scrubs of the west and centre of Australia. It had silky fur and, like other nail-tail wallabies, had a horny spur at the tip of its tail. Wikipedia

Crossarchus.label: Crossarchus
Crossarchus.description: Crossarchus is a genus of mongoose, commonly referred to as the kusimanse, mangue, or dwarf mongoose. Of three subfamilies of Herpestidae, the kusimanse is a member of Herpestinae or Mungotinae, which are small, highly social mongooses. Wikipedia

Cuvieronius.label: Cuvieronius
Cuvieronius.description: Cuvieronius is an extinct New World genus of gomphotheres. It is named after the French naturalist Georges Cuvier; it stood 2.7 m tall and looked like a modern elephant except for its spiral-shaped tusks. Wikipedia

Delacour's langur.label: Delacour's langur
Delacour's langur.description: The Delacour's langur, or Delacour's lutung, is a critically endangered species of lutung endemic to Vietnam. It is considered to be one of the world's most endangered primate species. Wikipedia

Deinotheriidae.label: Deinotheriidae
Deinotheriidae.description: Deinotheriidae is a family of prehistoric elephant-like proboscideans that lived during the Cenozoic era, first appearing in Africa, then spreading across southern Asia and Europe. Wikipedia

Dendromus.label: Dendromus
Dendromus.description: Mice in the genus Dendromus are commonly referred to as African climbing mice or tree mice, although these terms are often used to describe all members of the subfamily Dendromurinae. Wikipedia

Dian's tarsier.label: Dian's tarsier
Dian's tarsier.description: Dian's tarsier, also known as Diana tarsier, is a nocturnal primate found and endemic to central Sulawesi, Indonesia. Its head-body length is 11.5–12 centimetres and it has a tail of 22 centimetres. Dian's tarsier lives in rainforests. Wikipedia

Diademed sifaka.label: Diademed sifaka
Diademed sifaka.description: The diademed sifaka, or diademed simpona, is an endangered species of sifaka, one of the lemurs endemic to certain rainforests in eastern Madagascar. Wikipedia

Dinohippus.label: Dinohippus
Dinohippus.description: Dinohippus, is an extinct herbivorous mammal belonging to the tribe Equini, subfamily Equinae, which was endemic to North America from the late Hemphillian stage of the Miocene through the Zanclean ... Wikipedia

Dipodidae.label: Dipodidae
Dipodidae.description: The Dipodidae, or dipodids, are a family of rodents found across the northern hemisphere. This family includes over 50 species among the 16 genera. They include the jerboas, jumping mice, and birch mice. Wikipedia

Djungarian hamster.label: Djungarian hamster
Djungarian hamster.description: The Djungarian hamster, also known as the Siberian hamster or Russian winter white dwarf hamster, is one of three species of hamster in the genus Phodopus. Wikipedia

Dryas monkey.label: Dryas monkey
Dryas monkey.description: The Dryas monkey, also known as Salonga monkey or ntolu, is a little-known species of guenon found only in the Congo Basin, restricted to the left bank of the Congo River. Wikipedia

Eastern black crested gibbon.label: Eastern black crested gibbon
Eastern black crested gibbon.description: The eastern black crested gibbon, also known as the Cao-vit black crested gibbon or the Cao-vit crested gibbon, is a species of gibbon from southeast China and north Vietnam. Wikipedia

Eastern hare-wallaby.label: Eastern hare-wallaby
Eastern hare-wallaby.description: The eastern hare-wallaby once also known as the common hare wallaby, is an extinct species of wallaby that was native to southeastern Australia. It was first described by John Gould in 1841. Wikipedia

Eobasileus.label: Eobasileus
Eobasileus.description:
Eobasileus cornutus is an extinct species of dinocerate mammal.
Eobasileus was 4 metres long and stood 2.1 metres tall at the shoulder; and with a weight up to 4000 kg it was the largest Uintathere. Wikipedia

Eotitanops.label: Eotitanops
Eotitanops.description:
Eotitanops is an extinct genus of brontothere native to North America and Asia.
Eotitanops is the earliest known genus of brontothere. While brontotheres generally known as very large animals, Eotitanops was only 45 centimetres tall at the shoulder. Wikipedia

Eonycteris major.label: Eonycteris major
Eonycteris major.description: The greater nectar bat or greater dawn bat is a species of megabat within the genus Eonycteris. It is found in Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, and the Philippines. Wikipedia

Ethiopian dwarf mongoose.label: Ethiopian dwarf mongoose
Ethiopian dwarf mongoose.description: The Ethiopian dwarf mongoose, also known as the desert dwarf mongoose or Somali dwarf mongoose, is a mongoose found in eastern Africa, particularly Ethiopia, Kenya, and Somalia. Wikipedia

Eucladoceros.label: Eucladoceros
Eucladoceros.description: Eucladoceros or bush-antlered deer is an extinct genus of deer whose fossils have been discovered in Europe, the Middle East and Central Asia. Wikipedia

Euplerinae.label: Euplerinae
Euplerinae.description: Euplerinae is a subfamily of carnivorans that includes four species restricted to Madagascar. Together with the subfamily Galidiinae, which also only occurs on Madagascar, it forms the family Eupleridae. Wikipedia

Crateromys.label: Crateromys
Crateromys.description:
Crateromys is a genus of rodent, native to the Philippines, in the family Muridae. It contains four species
Dinagat Bushy-Tailed Cloud Rat
Giant Bushy-Tailed Cloud Rat
Panay Cloudrunner
Ilin Island Cloudrunner Wikipedia

Ferret-badger.label: Ferret-badger
Ferret-badger.description:
Ferret-badgers are the five species of mustelids of the genus Melogale.
Bornean Ferret-badger
Chinese Ferret-badger
Javan Ferret-badger
Burmese Ferret-badger
Vietnam Ferret-badger Wikipedia

Flying mouse.label: Flying mouse
Flying mouse.description: The flying mice, also known as the pygmy scaly-tails, pygmy scaly-tailed flying squirrels, or pygmy anomalures are not mice, not squirrels, and are not capable of true flight. Wikipedia

Fissipedia.label: Fissipedia
Fissipedia.description: Fissipedia is a former biological suborder comprising the largely land-based families of the order Carnivora. By and large, members of this suborder are meat-eaters, with the giant panda and red panda being the most notable exceptions. Wikipedia

Fork-marked lemur.label: Fork-marked lemur
Fork-marked lemur.description: Fork-marked lemurs or fork-crowned lemurs are four lemur species of the genus Phaner. Like all other lemurs, all species in this genus are native to Madagascar. Wikipedia

Formosan rock macaque.label: Formosan rock macaque
Formosan rock macaque.description: The Formosan rock macaque, Formosan rock monkey, or Taiwanese macaque, is a macaque endemic to the island of Taiwan and has been introduced to Japan. Besides humans, Formosan Rock Macaques are the only native primates living in Taiwan. Wikipedia

Funambulus.label: Funambulus
Funambulus.description:
Funambulus is a genus of rodent in the Sciuridae family.
It contains the following species
Genus Funambulus
Subgenus Funambulus
Layard's Palm Squirrel
Indian Palm Squirrel
Nilgiri Striped Palm Squirrel ... Wikipedia

Galidictis.label: Galidictis
Galidictis.description:
Galidictis is a genus of carnivoran in the family Eupleridae endemic to Madagascar. The name is from two ancient Greek words that both approximately mean ‘weasel’ galid- and iktis.
It contains the following species
Broad-striped Malagasy Mongoose. Wikipedia

Galidiinae.label: Galidiinae
Galidiinae.description: Galidiinae is a subfamily of carnivorans that is restricted to Madagascar and includes six species classified into four genera. Wikipedia

Galerella.label: Galerella
Galerella.description:
Galerella is a genus of mongooses native to Africa commonly called the slender mongooses.
There are four species in this genus
Angolan slender mongoose, Galerella flavescens
Somalian slender mongoose, ... Wikipedia
